---
title: Cancel Booking Flow — Microservices
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant TG as Telegram
    participant GW as bot-gateway
    participant BK as booking-service
    participant REDIS as Redis Streams

    User->>TG: /my_bookings
    TG->>GW: message /my_bookings
    GW->>BK: GET /bookings?telegramUserId=X
    BK-->>GW: bookings[]
    GW->>TG: sendMessage(bookings + [Cancel] buttons)

    User->>TG: click "Cancel: Library Desks"
    TG->>GW: callback cancel:booking-123
    GW->>TG: editMessage("Are you sure?", [Cancel booking] [Keep booking])

    alt User confirms
        User->>TG: click "Cancel booking"
        TG->>GW: callback cancel_confirm:booking-123
        GW->>BK: PATCH /bookings/booking-123 {status: "cancelled"}
        BK-->>GW: booking {status: "cancelled"}
        BK->>REDIS: publish booking.cancelled
        GW->>TG: editMessage("Booking cancelled: Library Desks ...")
    else User keeps booking
        User->>TG: click "Keep booking"
        TG->>GW: callback menu:bookings
        GW->>BK: GET /bookings?telegramUserId=X
        BK-->>GW: bookings[]
        GW->>TG: editMessage(bookings list)
    end
